<node id="paper:2005.14165">
  <data key="d0">Paper</data>
  <data key="d1">Language Models are Few-Shot Learners</data>
  <data key="d2">2005.14165</data>
  <data key="d3">Language Models are Few-Shot Learners</data>
  <data key="d4">["Tom B. Brown", "Benjamin Mann", "Nick Ryder"]</data>
  <data key="d5">We demonstrate that scaling language models greatly improves task-agnostic, few-shot performance, sometimes even reaching competitiveness with prior state-of-the-art fine-tuning approaches. Specifically, we train GPT-3, an autoregressive language model with 175 billion parameters, and test its performance in the few-shot setting.</data>
  <data key="d6">2020-05-28</data>
  <data key="d7">2026-03-04</data>
  <data key="d8">25000</data>
  <data key="d9">4335.83</data>
  <data key="d10">GPT-3 demonstrates that scaling language models greatly improves few-shot task performance.</data>
</node>
<node id="author:tom b. brown">
  <data key="d0">Author</data>
  <data key="d1">Tom B. Brown</data>
  <data key="d7">2026-03-04</data>
</node>
<node id="author:benjamin mann">
  <data key="d0">Author</data>
  <data key="d1">Benjamin Mann</data>
  <data key="d7">2026-03-04</data>
</node>
